dir. Brian Henson, 1992</h1>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>Charles Dickens’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780141195858" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">A Christmas Carol</a></em> (1843)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> Everybody Loves Muppets</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Dickens’s novella forever changed the way people related to Christmas, and it’s fitting that the Henson adaptation did the same thing for Millennials’ relationship to the holiday. Real fans never get sick of telling everyone in earshot that Michael Caine only agreed to be in the movie if he could play it as straight as Shakespeare. <em>–JF</em></p>
