<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>William Shakespeare’s <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780743477574" class="external" target="_blank"><em>The Taming of the Shrew</em></a> (c. 1592)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong>Witty Remarks • Not Another Teen Remake • Heath Ledger</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Ah, the ‘90s, when Hollywood went nuts mining classic literature to make teen movies. There were hits and there were misses, but one of the best was Karen McCullah Lutz and Kirsten Smith’s clever transformation of <em>The Taming of the Shrew</em>, which retains many of the play’s concerns (How should a woman be? What is the difference between how we present and who we are? What is love worth, no like literally, in dollars?) and has enough wordplay to thrill the Bard himself, but makes it all deliciously modern (and makes these answers to those questions much more palatable). Plus, it’s stuffed with Millennial culture royalty: Heath Ledger, Julia Stiles, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, <del>Alex Mack</del> Larisa Oleynik, Gabrielle Union, David Krumholtz. A classic. –<em>ET</em></p>
