<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong>Love Jo All Your Days • True To The Novel • I Guess This Is Growing Up</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I love Greta Gerwig, but there’s just something so cozy about Gillian Armstrong’s take on the March girls. And for a story in thrall to the wonder years, I would think coziness is the point. The bits after Beth’s death hit especially hard once we’ve sung all those carols around the piano, and hurled snowballs over a Christmas-y Thomas Newman soundtrack. Final snaps must be given to Claire Danes, who brought such tenderness to the easily undersold Beth. And of course the unruly Winona, a perfect Jo. <em>–BA</em></p>
