<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #b23233;"><em><strong><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="269458" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-is-the-best-literary-film-adaptation-of-the-last-50-years/apocalypsenow-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="800,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="apocalypsenow copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-269458" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/apocalypsenow-copy-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" />Apocalypse Now</strong></em></span><br />
dir. Francis Ford Coppola, 1979</h1>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>Joseph Conrad’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780141441672" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Heart of Darkness</a></em> (1899) and Michael Herr&#8217;s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679735250" class="external" target="_blank">Dispatches</a></em> (1977)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> Almost Directed By George Lucas?! • T.S. Eliot Quotes • Big Music Choices</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Perhaps the best Vietnam War movie ever made. A savvy translation from the source material by Francis Ford Coppola and right-wing crank John Milius, <em>Apocalypse Now</em> shifts Conrad’s tale of depravity set amidst Belgian colonial horrors to a tale of depravity set amidst American imperial horrors in Vietnam and Cambodia.</p>
<p>An elite soldier with a fraying mind is sent deep into a wartime nightmare, and the sweaty performances, bold musical choices, and beautiful cinematography take us there. And every film nerd knows that the production’s depravity and delirium almost surpasses the film’s—<em>Apocalypse Now</em>’s Wikipedia page is as wild as the film itself.<em> –JF</em></p>
