<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #b23233;"><em><strong><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="269472" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-is-the-best-literary-film-adaptation-of-the-last-50-years/englishpatient/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient.jpg" data-orig-size="800,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="englishpatient" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-269472" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/englishpatient-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" />The English Patient</strong></em></span><br />
dir. Anthony Minghella, 1996</h1>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>Michael Ondaatje’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679745204" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The English Patient</a></em> (1992)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> So Many Awards • Sexy Archaeology • Biplanes</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I got an undergraduate degree in archaeology and a lot of my peers cited Indiana Jones or <em>The Mummy</em> as the source of their interest in the field, but I distinctly remember one person saying they were inspired by <em>The English Patient</em>. And they&#8217;re not wrong—the movie certainly made archaeology seem like it would involve a lot more falling in love in beautiful caves.</p>
<p>This movie yearns, oh how it yearns. It&#8217;s the careful pacing, and the movement through time that builds the feeling, and allows <em>The English Patient</em> to maintain the careful attention of the novel, not easy to pull off with so much fighting going on. Minghella and a stellar cast never lose the tenderness amidst the epic sweep of a world war. –<em>JF</em></p>
