</span></strong><strong>MATCHUP: </strong></h1>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>The Silence of the Lambs</em> (1) vs. <em>Devil in a Blue Dress</em> (16)</strong></h1>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: #b23233;">******************************************</span></strong></h1>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #b23233;"><em><strong><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="269480" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-is-the-best-literary-film-adaptation-of-the-last-50-years/silenceofthelambs-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="800,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="silenceofthelambs copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-269480" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/silenceofthelambs-copy-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" />The Silence of the Lambs</strong></em></span><br />
dir. Jonathan Demme, 1991</h1>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>Thomas Harris’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250048097" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Silence of the Lambs</a></em> (1988)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> Ruined Both Chianti AND Fava Beans • And the Song &#8220;American Girl&#8221; • Still Worth It, Though</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Jonathan Demme&#8217;s adaptation starts out tense (dreary woods and Howard Shore strings from the jump) and tightens the screws, with surgical precision, to an almost unbearable tautness—culminating in one of the great payoffs in film history. And, of course, the repartee (if slightly mismatched) between Jodie Foster and Anthony Hopkins is a skin-crawling delight. <em>–JG</em></p>
