<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #b23233;"><em><strong><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="269483" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-is-the-best-literary-film-adaptation-of-the-last-50-years/devilinabluedress-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="800,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="devilinabluedress copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-269483" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/devilinabluedress-copy-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" />Devil in a Blue Dress</strong></em></span><br />
dir. Carl Franklin, 1995</h1>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>Walter Mosley’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781982150341" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devil in a Blue Dress</a></em> (1990)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> It Goes Higher Than You Could <em>Ever</em> Imagine • Denzel’s Cool Mustache • L.A. At Night</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This neo-noir, based on Walter Mosley&#8217;s debut, is incredibly stylish. The ear for dialogue that makes Mosley’s writing so distinct is a natural fit for the screen, and it comes to life with an excellent cast led by Denzel Washington at the height of his powers as Easy Rawlins. As in all truly great noirs, Easy is a cork adrift in larger social and political forces, and Denzel is just as good at being shocked as he is at being forceful and charismatic. Plus everyone looks cool as hell in all the moody nighttime fog, which is exactly what you want visually from an L.A. crime story. <em>–JF</em></p>
