<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>Roderick Thorp’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781935169185" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nothing Lasts Forever</a></em> (1979)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> But Is It a Christmas Movie? • Better Than the Book • The Watch is a Metaphor, You See • Yippie-ki-yay</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>An action movie about a cop at a Christmas party that turned out way, way better than it needed to be, thanks to Bruce Willis, the always-excellent Alan Rickman, superb pacing, and most of all, a strong sense of humor. Is it essentially an anti-feminist parable? Possibly! But you&#8217;d hardly notice because of all the fun you&#8217;re having. <em>–ET</em></p>
